==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dulcimer
<hw>Dul"ci*mer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.
<ets>dolcemele</ets>,r Sp. <ets>dulcemele</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>dulcis</ets> sweet + <ets>melos</ets> song, melody, Gr. <?/; cf.
OF. <ets>doulcemele</ets>. See <er>Dulcet</er>, and
<er>Melody</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>An
instrument, having stretched metallic wires which are beaten with two
light hammers held in the hands of the performer.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>An ancient musical instrument in use among the Jews. <au>Dan. iii.
5.</au> It is supposed to be the same with the psaltery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

